2.00	Robert_Frost_Trail	Robert Frost Trail (Massachusetts)	The Robert Frost Trail is a 47-mile (76 km) long footpath that passes through the eastern Connecticut River Valley of Massachusetts. The trail runs from the Connecticut River in South Hadley, Massachusetts to Ruggles Pond in Wendell State Forest, through both Hampshire and Franklin County and includes a number of scenic features such as the Holyoke Range, Mount Orient, Puffer's Pond, and Mount Toby. The trail is named after the poet Robert Frost, who lived and taught in the area from 1916 to 1938.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/41/Bare_Mountain_-_Mount_Holyoke_Range.jpg/250px-Bare_Mountain_-_Mount_Holyoke_Range.jpg
